latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#incollaboration Oh what a meaningful video , the word fussy at first make me think, am I one ?
Then I remembered on yes, when I wanted to help my child to self feed , people did think and tell me, eventually everyone eats why the fuss, you can feed him now and he will do self feeding later, that’s exactly what’s shown in the video. @firstcryindia has exactly depicted the same via their video , it's absolutely fine for the mom to decide what she chooses ,and  #fussisok, Thankyou @firstcryindia to show this and communicate to so many out there.

All my mommy friends out there watch the video and comment on the main idea. 
👍which moment is the most relatable ?
👍what are you fussy about? 
👍Do they think #FussyIsFantastic?

latestIgtvVideos.title: First air travel with a 17month old
BLW my experience
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ever since I had a baby of my own, and i had heard people tell me , feeding baby will take up your life . My mom and mom in law would tell me tales how my husband and me both were picky eaters.
My research begun then, I came across BLW and the various benefits of it. One of it was, it may avoid a picky eater, and well I thought to give it a try and if it doesn’t work after a certain time frame, I would do the traditional one. 
And oh boy , it worked like a charm....
Hence, these are my views and experience on baby led weaning.
In the hope , that by my experience someone might want to try it, and helps them in their journey.
Having said that please read , educate yourself and choose the best for your family !

Healthy chocolate 🍫 
Take 20 almonds + 20 cashew + 30 makkana, dry roast them !

Blend them coarsely, now add 7/8 dates , few raisins and blend them all in to make a mushy texture !

Set them in a silicon mould ,in the fridge for 10-15 mins.

Take them out from the mould.

Dip it with dark chocolate.

Set them in fridge for 30 minutes.

Your healthy chocolate is ready !
Healthy: dark chocolate = antioxidant and magnesium , nuts =good fats , vitamin and minerals , no added refine sugar !

🫙Store it in the fridge for Upto a month 🍫

Thankyou @bharti.laughterqueen , this was genius 🍫

Easy healthy recipes that can be stored !

🍪Easy Aata Barfi 
Ingredients:
	•	1 cup wheat flour (aata)
	•	1/2 cup ghee (clarified butter)
	•	3/4 cup jaggery 
	•	1/4 tsp cardamom powder ( optional )
	•	Chopped nuts (optional)
✅
	•	Heat ghee in a pan.
	•	Add wheat flour.
	•	Cook on low heat, stir continuously until golden brown and smells nice.
Cool a bit:
	•	Turn off the heat.
	•	Add jaggery and cardamom powder.
	•	Spread the mix on a greased plate.
	•	Flatten it.
	•	Add chopped nuts on top (optional)
	•	Let it cool and set.
	•	Cut into pieces and enjoy!

🍬 Dry Fruit Laddu

Ingredients:
	•	1 cup seedless dates (blended into a puree)
	•	1/4 cup cashews
	•	1/4 cup almonds
	•	2 tbsp pistachios (optional)
	•	2 tbsp raisins
	•	1–2 tbsp ghee
✅
	1.	Chop all dry fruits.
	2.	Roast them in ghee till golden.
	3.	Add date puree . Mix well.
	4.	Cool slightly, then roll into laddus
